## Claude Code

- Do not rely on Claude auto-memory in this repository. Use the QSL document store as the shared memory system.
- Use `qsl:read("SKILL.md")` at session start, then follow its bootstrap instructions and tool conventions before reading repo-specific engineering state.
- Session-start state documents live in QSL by document ID (`research/agQSL/engineering-state.md`, `agents/engineering/users/{email}.md`, `agents/engineering/current-state.md`); do not expect them in the local checkout.
- Specialist agent memory lives under `agents/<agentname>/...` in QSL. Local `.claude/agent-memory/...` files are local scratch state only and are not the source of truth.


