The `/permissions` proposal is built on a shaky assumption: the changelog item says the **slash command** understands named permission profiles. It does not prove that unattended subprocess calls can use `codex --profile ro-summary`, nor that profiles enforce filesystem and shell restrictions in non-TUI runs.

That matters because **mopsus mostly needs headless safety**, not prettier interactive permission display.

## Counterarguments

- `/permissions` is a UI/control-plane feature, while the proposed pilot is a daemon/runtime feature. Wrong surface.
